aradoxically, economic growth—is ever rising private debt. The paradox is that while debt is essential and our economy relies on it, it also brings instability unless it is periodically deleveraged—and that is very hard to do. It can, however, be carefully managed, and Vague ends the book by showing how to do so in policy areas ranging from trade and housing to financial policy and student debt.Underpinned by pioneering data analysis and the author’s lifetime of experience in the financial world, this book is essential for anyone who wants to understand the deep, underlying dynamics of the American economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDebt. 0aFinance, Personal. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / General.2bisacsh  aDebt.  aGDP.  aassets.  abalance sheet.  abanking.  acompany shares.  acovid.  ade-leveraging.  adebt exploitation.  adebt jubilee.  adeficit.  aeconomic growth.  aeconomic inequality.  aequity.  afinance.  afinancial crisis.  afinancial policy.  agovernment program.  ahousehold debt.  ahousehold income.  ahousing policy.  ainflation.  ainvestments.  aloan forgiveness.  amortgage.  anet worth.  apolicy recommendations.  aprivate debt.  apublic debt.  areal estate.  astock market.  astudent loan.  aunderserved communities.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2023 Englishz978311131907008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2023z9783111318134oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Press Complete eBook-Pa